downloadTitle: Project Management sample diagram for Visio 2010
downloadDescription: Learn how you can get a visual overview of your data with this Visio 2010 PivotDiagram sample diagram.
detailsSection:
Use this Microsoft Visio 2010 sample diagram to see how you could analyze and summarize project data in a visual, easy-to-understand format. This sample shows how the PivotDiagram functionality in Visio can be used to create a hierarchical view of project data. The diagram automatically generates based on a linked or embedded data set. 

This sample diagram uses embedded shape data to illustrate two views of how a firm’s efforts to recruit new hires are progressing (by unfilled positions and by recruiter). The embedded shapes used in this sample could also be used to build a scorecard that shows the status of virtually any project or ongoing work stream, such as customer support effectiveness or sales performance.
installInstructionSection: Click Download to save the sample diagram to your computer.
